    <node id="Reducers">
      <data key="d0">Reducers</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Reducers are fittings that reduce the size of pipes and are detailed in paragraphs 6.2.3 and 6.4.2.2.&lt;SEP&gt;Reducers are fittings that reduce the diameter of a pipe.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1c16e04b6fef5dddbccafe35258da63d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255059</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Eccentric Reducers">
      <data key="d0">Eccentric Reducers</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Eccentric Reducers are fittings that reduce the diameter of a pipe while offsetting the centerline, with dimensions specified in the standard.&lt;SEP&gt;Eccentric reducers are a specific type of reducer and are detailed in paragraphs 6.2.3 and 6.4.2.2.&lt;SEP&gt;Eccentric Reducers are reducers where the axis of the reduced section is offset from the axis of the full-size section.&lt;SEP&gt;Eccentric reducers are fittings that reduce the size of pipes or tubes while maintaining a non-circular cross-section.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1c16e04b6fef5dddbccafe35258da63d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79385a11135d33465afc630658dca15b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255059</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Straight Sizes">
      <data key="d0">Straight Sizes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Straight Sizes refer to the standard sizes of fittings without reductions or offsets, as detailed in the standard.&lt;SEP&gt;Straight sizes are applicable for certain dimensions and are detailed in note (3).&lt;SEP&gt;Straight Sizes refer to standard pipe sizes without reductions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1c16e04b6fef5dddbccafe35258da63d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79385a11135d33465afc630658dca15b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255059</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ring Joint Groove">
      <data key="d0">Ring Joint Groove</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Ring joint groove is a feature applied to flanges to facilitate certain types of connections.&lt;SEP&gt;Ring Joint Groove is a specific type of joint used in pipe connections, described in the equations for bolt length calculations.&lt;SEP&gt;Ring Joint Groove is a feature in flange joints where a gasket is seated, with dimensions provided in the standard.&lt;SEP&gt;Ring joint groove dimensions are provided in Table II-5 of Mandatory Appendix II.&lt;SEP&gt;Ring Joint Groove is a groove around the circumference of a flange for sealing purposes.&lt;SEP&gt;Ring joint groove is a groove for a ring joint seal.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1c16e04b6fef5dddbccafe35258da63d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-168613df3512c6ad1c5f5bdc4c21ec22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9465f39ee050c9785a9cb1b6547a93ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79385a11135d33465afc630658dca15b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255059</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ring Joint Facing Dimensions">
      <data key="d0">Ring Joint Facing Dimensions</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Ring joint facing dimensions are specific measurements for ring joint flanges.&lt;SEP&gt;Ring Joint Facing Dimensions are the specific dimensions for the ring joint grooves in flange joints, as provided in the standard.&lt;SEP&gt;Ring Joint Facing Dimensions are specific dimensions related to the ring joint groove.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1c16e04b6fef5dddbccafe35258da63d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-168613df3512c6ad1c5f5bdc4c21ec22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79385a11135d33465afc630658dca15b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255059</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Flange Edge">
      <data key="d0">Flange Edge</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Flange Edge is the outer edge of a flange.&lt;SEP&gt;Flange Edge is the outer edge of a flange, with specific dimensions given in the standard.&lt;SEP&gt;Flange edges are referenced in the table and are part of the dimensions for fittings.&lt;SEP&gt;Flange Edge is the edge of a flange where it connects to a pipe.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1c16e04b6fef5dddbccafe35258da63d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79385a11135d33465afc630658dca15b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-944868763ad488938d4bbbf02d4db395</data>
