    <node id="Class 150">
      <data key="d0">Class 150</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Class 150 is a pressure rating class for flanges, specifically defined in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard. This class is used for pipe flanges and fittings, including ring-joint facings, and is part of the ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code. Class 150 components have a minimum design pressure of 150 pounds per square inch, addressing dimensional conflicts in flange facings. This rating class is crucial for ensuring the safe operation of pressure vessels and piping systems by providing standardized specifications for flanges and fittings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e9b794842bd12c52a5bc301b6368bc29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c2f5be5ae1269254713641c236d6a28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4ca239f2a2d5f7e2ab87708ca342046&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7d037c7aa1de140eef228e3b5f72b1a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc67612f135316380b75df378379082b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-29a21b64670fd3044048fc8ebefbb64a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a46bab0c67076b2880139ab335aeabc3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-037e87f32d950a93e4afb57afbe8ac81</data>
