    <node id="IHS">
      <data key="d0">IHS</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">IHS is the organization that provides access to ASME standards and documents under license. Specifically, IHS offers licensing for the reproduction and networking of documents, including the ASME B16.5-2013 standard. This involves providing copyrighted material, licensed copies of documents, and licensing services for ASME materials and standards. IHS acts as the licensing provider for ASME standards, ensuring that users have the necessary permissions to access and use the data. Additionally, IHS is responsible for providing the document under license from ASME International and ensuring that the copyright information and notices are correctly managed. Overall, IHS plays a crucial role in facilitating the distribution and use of ASME standards and documents through its licensing services.</data>
