    <node id="ASME B16.5-2013">
      <data key="d0">ASME B16.5-2013</data>
      <data key="d1">standard</data>
      <data key="d2">ASME B16.5-2013 is a standard document published by ASME International, which provides comprehensive specifications for pipe flanges and flanged fittings. This standard covers pressure-temperature ratings, materials, dimensions, and testing methods for various classes of flanges and fittings, including Class 150, 300, 400, 600, 900, 1500, and 2500. It also includes guidelines for flange bolt dimensions and recommendations, as well as specifications for flanged and threaded fittings. The document has been updated from the 2009 version and includes changes identified by margin notes and errata. Additionally, it contains detailed specifications for flange facing finishes, ring-joint facing dimensions, and welding specifications. ASME B16.5-2013 is referenced in various documents and texts for its pressure-temperature ratings and specifications for pipe flanges and法兰附件。</data>
