    <node id="NPS">
      <data key="d0">NPS</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Nominal Pipe Size (NPS) is a standard designation used in the industry to specify the size of pipes, flanges, and flanged fittings. This standard is employed for identifying pipe, flange, or flanged fitting end connection sizes and dimensions. NPS provides a consistent method for measuring and specifying pipe diameters, ensuring compatibility and uniformity across various applications and industries.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-97928cdda56c6d8001d765f6c620a3de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4ca239f2a2d5f7e2ab87708ca342046&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99a1e3e75d92d69d9c4e1104e9aee33d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5bd9113edf820112d3129b64eaf2d88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00bcbf709205575d1058a0d877e0be98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aa3224b393530e878cd8da41ea17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a41e880ec9f7ddef8b2a387e71dbd6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1991062d5c6aa490277d1b30a0762cee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0df2a48018c5815fcbc69ee77e5e9629&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55a057d80d0d30bec149f947f43931d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-944868763ad488938d4bbbf02d4db395&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3abc323d58495b8071ec97d17500fa8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60a005b1fe0813d5a804046b9814c9ae</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255065</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ring Joint">
      <data key="d0">Ring Joint</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Ring Joint is a type of flange joint used in pipe connections and fittings. It is specifically designed to fit around a pipe and is mentioned in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard. Ring Joint is characterized by its specific dimensions, particularly the lap thickness after machining, which ensures proper fit and functionality in piping systems. This joint design is also noted for its use in Class 600 flanged fittings and various types of flanged fittings and joints used in the construction of piping systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a82ed5c06f52a3dac4b42b7d20165f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97928cdda56c6d8001d765f6c620a3de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a2d9b2e3cbcac399e69cd4ddd026d10&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fa036517d95c30255cdfda4bb900973d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76864809d8f49cc522affb8d29d2289a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b78e83615026fe67e2233586fc3ce5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3183da68eed473652f2a88bb963447&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31bc32875a6306edfc4741462637a4e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bcc460a90a8e17448e1e385e1599c80d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b58a0b8fcb69d1ec44e63ba6135c5ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b3d3983136bf26d485546eb760e1ee8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-770491ae4c5f3e5340337d3d781061d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d62708c76d7807fe7760eab56bea6043&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38e654cf4e95cce3ba3e7cced9c476f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7d66f91fd341a23e68eadbefdb9b7ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55a057d80d0d30bec149f947f43931d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-944868763ad488938d4bbbf02d4db395&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b2ad87c358f78ef6fe44833b9f86e79</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255065</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Raised Face">
      <data key="d0">Raised Face</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Raised Face is a type of flange face design where the sealing surface is raised above the flange face, typically rising above the nominal pipe diameter or the bolt circle. This design is commonly used in pipe fittings and is specified in various standards, including the ASME B16.5-2013. Raised Face is also mentioned in tables and documents detailing flange face configurations and dimensions. This type of flange face is specifically designed to enhance sealing capabilities by providing a raised surface that aligns with the mating flange, ensuring a secure and effective seal.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-97928cdda56c6d8001d765f6c620a3de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7cf8cbd7624104560bfb71708f6cc010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10054c6a90c7e34cf9ec3260463671fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bcc460a90a8e17448e1e385e1599c80d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79385a11135d33465afc630658dca15b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b198cbe23ec845253cfd2861d7fc5756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-254e0b50334d5302f82bd70beda43312&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d62708c76d7807fe7760eab56bea6043&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7d66f91fd341a23e68eadbefdb9b7ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3abc323d58495b8071ec97d17500fa8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b2ad87c358f78ef6fe44833b9f86e79</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Intersecting Centerlines">
      <data key="d0">Intersecting Centerlines</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Intersecting centerlines are detailed in paragraph 6.2.4.&lt;SEP&gt;Intersecting centerlines refer to the intersection points of centerlines in fittings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Center- to-Contact Surface">
      <data key="d0">Center- to-Contact Surface</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Center-to-contact surface dimensions measure the distance from the center to the contact surface.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Center- to-End Dimensions">
      <data key="d0">Center- to-End Dimensions</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Center-to-end dimensions measure the distance from the center to the end of a component.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Side Outlet Fittings">
      <data key="d0">Side Outlet Fittings</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Side Outlet Fittings are fittings with outlets on the side.&lt;SEP&gt;Side outlet fittings are components with outlets on the side.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00bcbf709205575d1058a0d877e0be98</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ISBN 978-0-7918-3491-6">
      <data key="d0">ISBN 978-0-7918-3491-6</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">ISBN 978-0-7918-349</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Center- to-Flange Edge">
      <data key="d0">Center- to-Flange Edge</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Center-to-flange edge dimensions measure the distance from the center to the edge of a flange.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Flange Edge- to-Flange Edge">
      <data key="d0">Flange Edge- to-Flange Edge</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Flange edge-to-flange edge dimensions measure the distance between the edges of two flanges.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Taper Hub">
      <data key="d0">Taper Hub</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Taper Hub is a conical section that connects pipes of different diameters.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9897cde782cd9c636d94d997a0270bee</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Nominal Wall Thickness">
      <data key="d0">Nominal Wall Thickness</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Nominal Wall Thickness is a standard measurement used for pipe walls.&lt;SEP&gt;Nominal Wall Thickness is the standard measurement of a pipe's wall thickness.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9897cde782cd9c636d94d997a0270bee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b3d3983136bf26d485546eb760e1ee8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Welding End">
      <data key="d0">Welding End</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Welding End is the end of a pipe prepared for welding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9897cde782cd9c636d94d997a0270bee</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Welding Neck Flange">
      <data key="d0">Welding Neck Flange</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Welding Neck Flange is a type of flange with a short section of pipe attached to it.&lt;SEP&gt;Welding neck flange is a type of flange described in Table 16, characterized by a hub and bore.&lt;SEP&gt;Welding Neck Flange is a type of flange with a long neck that allows for welding to a pipe.&lt;SEP&gt;Welding Neck Flange is a type of flange with a neck that allows for welding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9897cde782cd9c636d94d997a0270bee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b5b0e2acae20a65c1c3b15054804a3f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a41e880ec9f7ddef8b2a387e71dbd6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1991062d5c6aa490277d1b30a0762cee</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Backing Ring">
      <data key="d0">Backing Ring</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Backing Ring is a metal ring used to support the weld during fabrication.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9897cde782cd9c636d94d997a0270bee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b12c53c23345ed4fe1a5bec6911cbcd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="True Y">
      <data key="d0">True Y</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">True Y is a type of flanged fitting used in piping systems. It is mentioned in various documents and standards, including the ASME B16.5-2013 standard. True Y refers to a configuration in piping systems where three pipes meet at a point, forming a Y shape. This fitting is also listed in tables and documents related to piping systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-97928cdda56c6d8001d765f6c620a3de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7d58ff493a61d09e2e197daaae3dce3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76864809d8f49cc522affb8d29d2289a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7cf8cbd7624104560bfb71708f6cc010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3183da68eed473652f2a88bb963447&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-254e0b50334d5302f82bd70beda43312&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38e654cf4e95cce3ba3e7cced9c476f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7d66f91fd341a23e68eadbefdb9b7ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b2ad87c358f78ef6fe44833b9f86e79</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ASME B16.25">
      <data key="d0">ASME B16.25</data>
      <data key="d1">standard</data>
      <data key="d2">ASME B16.25 is a standard for welding neck flanges and socket weld flanges.&lt;SEP&gt;ASME B16.25 provides detailed dimensions for pipe fittings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9897cde782cd9c636d94d997a0270bee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c778385453fdf92adad309927fd92426</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fig. 1">
      <data key="d0">Fig. 1</data>
      <data key="d1">figure</data>
      <data key="d2">Fig. 1 is a diagram showing the inside contour for use with rectangular backing rings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9897cde782cd9c636d94d997a0270bee</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255066</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
