    <node id="Flange">
      <data key="d0">Flange</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Flange is a circular rim or collar around the end of a pipe or tube, used to connect it to another pipe or fitting. This component is commonly found in piping systems and is often made of metal. Flanges serve to join pipes or tubes, providing a secure and leak-proof connection. They are typically characterized by a raised face design, which facilitates the use of gaskets to ensure a tight seal. Flanges are integral parts of pipe fittings, mentioned in various contexts as components used in pipe connections and ducts. These components are essential in ensuring the proper functioning and safety of piping systems in various industries.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-97928cdda56c6d8001d765f6c620a3de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9897cde782cd9c636d94d997a0270bee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7d58ff493a61d09e2e197daaae3dce3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2904771c0741938726758dab221ea2fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c2f5be5ae1269254713641c236d6a28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99a1e3e75d92d69d9c4e1104e9aee33d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7cf8cbd7624104560bfb71708f6cc010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1991062d5c6aa490277d1b30a0762cee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b3b645868407aac7a7956cba998d0e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b3d3983136bf26d485546eb760e1ee8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-944868763ad488938d4bbbf02d4db395&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6962408b774fe5ab78bfedcf807dfe29</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255068</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Temp.,  °F">
      <data key="d0">Temp.,  °F</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Temp.,  °F is a temperature scale used in pressure ratings.&lt;SEP&gt;Temp.,  °F is the temperature column in the table.&lt;SEP&gt;Temp.,  °F is a concept referring to temperature in Fahrenheit.&lt;SEP&gt;Temp.,  °F, refers to the temperature in Fahrenheit for which the pressure ratings are given.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a0109166d44b4066c639726c7a8ccb61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503d8a63fb788455f42315bb7625264d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64169122dd60bf0873c761d69e140ea8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27f045cb711599e1626ae4544de66292</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255068</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dimensions">
      <data key="d0">Dimensions</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Dimensions specify the physical measurements of a component, which are crucial for ensuring proper fit and function. These dimensions are particularly important for pipe flanges and flanged fittings, as they are standardized to ensure compatibility and safety. According to the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, dimensions include specific measurements and specifications for ring-joint facings, such as the Class 1500 Flanged Fittings. Dimensions encompass various aspects of flanges, including hub diameter, minimum corner bore, and other critical measurements. These dimensions are typically provided in inches for different fittings and parts, ensuring precise manufacturing and installation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92cbd143b7fb7a0985b6ba383ca2f7ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b74fa9e1989b40d422a2e7a6a04ea958&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5a59c9e110a47eb7eef51fb2fb81c5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65bb92edfd06205fa901097f136f3ce0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-944868763ad488938d4bbbf02d4db395&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d659b8d39a7ddb50dd478cba4c619fa3</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255068</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tolerances">
      <data key="d0">Tolerances</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Tolerances define acceptable variations in component dimensions, particularly for fittings such as pipe flanges and flanged fittings. These tolerances are detailed in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, specifically in section 7, where they are discussed and revised. Tolerances for flanges are specified for certain dimensions, allowing for permissible limits of variation in their dimensions. These specifications are crucial for ensuring the proper fit and function of flanges and other fittings in various applications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92cbd143b7fb7a0985b6ba383ca2f7ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ea1b2e76d1f000d5569b9486b9e5ac4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98e6bd64e65f31d06ced3b3e90f47312&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5a59c9e110a47eb7eef51fb2fb81c5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65bb92edfd06205fa901097f136f3ce0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00bcbf709205575d1058a0d877e0be98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255069</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Facings">
      <data key="d0">Facings</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Facings are the surfaces of fittings, specifically flanges, that come into contact with other parts, such as gaskets or other flanges or pipes. These surfaces are detailed in paragraph 6.4 of the ASME B16.5-2013 standard and are often subject to specific requirements and treatments or finishes to ensure proper functionality and sealing. Facings play a crucial role in ensuring the integrity and performance of flange connections by providing a surface that can effectively engage with gaskets or adjacent flanges.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ea1b2e76d1f000d5569b9486b9e5ac4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98e6bd64e65f31d06ced3b3e90f47312&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd9487a2f3662945039d8bc799ee92b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65bb92edfd06205fa901097f136f3ce0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00bcbf709205575d1058a0d877e0be98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1991062d5c6aa490277d1b30a0762cee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255069</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Flange Bolt Holes">
      <data key="d0">Flange Bolt Holes</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Flange Bolt Holes are the holes in flanges where bolts are inserted and passed through to secure the flange to another flange or a pipe. These holes are described in various documents, including paragraph 6.5 and Table 19, as well as in Mandatory Appendix II, specifically in paragraph 6.5 and Table II-17. Flange bolt holes are essential for the assembly and connection of flanges in piping systems, ensuring a secure and reliable joint.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4797fefc55d99753aacd5d36c1d642f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98e6bd64e65f31d06ced3b3e90f47312&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edfa2a8d33668f4d57dbfceea1fab17e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65bb92edfd06205fa901097f136f3ce0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00bcbf709205575d1058a0d877e0be98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1991062d5c6aa490277d1b30a0762cee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e063d28a217c52dd27cce9855642fcf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfef7ffcc548c36b5c0ed0c4c060dedd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Class">
      <data key="d0">Class</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Class is a designation for pressure-temperature ratings in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, serving as a category in the tables that specifies different pressure ratings. This concept refers to the different pressure classes and is used in pressure ratings, indicating the classification of materials based on their pressure-temperature ratings. Class is also a classification of working pressures shown in the table, representing various categories of working pressures in the document.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a0109166d44b4066c639726c7a8ccb61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba38e995e9267b01b62ee7faaf352b6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4ca239f2a2d5f7e2ab87708ca342046&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503d8a63fb788455f42315bb7625264d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64169122dd60bf0873c761d69e140ea8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-faa44ee0ab9a603579ea4693825fe3ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e5cd3565858655527cd4c1e3bec3a75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b80a9d659f34e9872ec7554628906bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27f045cb711599e1626ae4544de66292&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7575423eeeae0b9d1868c3a0607f0f9</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="1,500">
      <data key="d0">1,500</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">1,500 is a working pressure class in pounds per square inch gauge (psig).&lt;SEP&gt;1,500 is a temperature value in the table.&lt;SEP&gt;1,500 is a pressure temperature rating for a specific material group in ASME B16.5-2013.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a0109166d44b4066c639726c7a8ccb61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-844bac183fd8bd250a40261dfc4c11b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3418e404eea4379f09843151bbf0eaf</data>
