      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Reducer">
      <data key="d0">Reducer</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Reducer is a type of fitting used in piping systems, specifically designed to connect pipes of different diameters. This fitting can be either a reducer or a type of flanged fitting, as mentioned in various documents and standards. According to the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, reducers are described as fitting types for flanged fittings, which are crucial components in ensuring the proper connection and flow of fluids or gases through piping systems. Reducers are also referenced in dimensions tables and standard documents, highlighting their importance in maintaining system integrity and efficiency.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d6cca9b47ec0107e466518239551dc0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a2d9b2e3cbcac399e69cd4ddd026d10&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76864809d8f49cc522affb8d29d2289a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00bcbf709205575d1058a0d877e0be98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-138e3a0b2ec6167487d8efd84636fa5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b198cbe23ec845253cfd2861d7fc5756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b58a0b8fcb69d1ec44e63ba6135c5ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-254e0b50334d5302f82bd70beda43312&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b2ad87c358f78ef6fe44833b9f86e79</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="275">
      <data key="d0">275</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">275 is a temperature value in the table.&lt;SEP&gt;275 is a working pressure value for the material at a specific temperature and class.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a0109166d44b4066c639726c7a8ccb61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64169122dd60bf0873c761d69e140ea8</data>
