    <node id="425°C">
      <data key="d0">425°C</data>
      <data key="d1">temperature</data>
      <data key="d2">425°C is a temperature threshold beyond which certain materials may undergo undesirable phase changes.&lt;SEP&gt;425°C is a temperature threshold for certain materials, beyond which specific phase conversions may occur.&lt;SEP&gt;425°C is a temperature limit mentioned in the notes for the use of certain materials.&lt;SEP&gt;425°C is a temperature threshold mentioned in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard.&lt;SEP&gt;425°C is the maximum temperature limit for using Solution Annealed Material.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c01da93e68a62ebd162469f786517eea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fffba15a554e990d12d9e92c9fbc0bc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a319dec7b0b61a0bc319c91c99c9a587&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d2c522c8854e3aa2e96dab1c0fb5599&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f64edd2488182d1fe2576b6fcef9b20</data>
