    <node id="Graphite">
      <data key="d0">Graphite</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Graphite is a form of carbon that can result from carbide phase conversion.&lt;SEP&gt;Graphite is a material that may form upon prolonged exposure to temperatures above 425°C.&lt;SEP&gt;Graphite is a material that may form from the carbide phase of steel upon prolonged exposure to high temperatures.&lt;SEP&gt;Graphite is the product of the conversion of the carbide phase of carbon–molybdenum steel at temperatures above 465°C.&lt;SEP&gt;Graphite is the product of the conversion of the carbide phase of carbon–molybdenum steel at temperatures above 875°F.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c01da93e68a62ebd162469f786517eea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fffba15a554e990d12d9e92c9fbc0bc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d852b8bef4bf5e1b06d5eca4665efb0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7040bbb99f12a42660ed8b6b948c1e9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47bb2fa75b3e7cd5e145f1d353440450</data>
