    <node id="carbon content">
      <data key="d0">carbon content</data>
      <data key="d1">attribute</data>
      <data key="d2">carbon content is a factor considered for material usage above 538°C.&lt;SEP&gt;carbon content refers to the percentage of carbon in the material, specifically noted to be 0.04% or higher at temperatures over 538°C.&lt;SEP&gt;carbon content refers to the percentage of carbon in materials.&lt;SEP&gt;Carbon content is a measure of the amount of carbon in materials, particularly important for determining material suitability at high temperatures.&lt;SEP&gt;Carbon content is a critical attribute for material usage specifications, particularly at temperatures over 1,000°F.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4934fb4fb5cf186041d1e2a713f09ddd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eba111d15c9ea294f7b9b8b23ba5ca79&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0da4a394d3be37c8a59a24dd838d13b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8689b4c902ee495b0f8e912c7a0a9582&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-913ab8bf8d15091a1c354835260c5873</data>
