      <data key="d2">1,000°F is a temperature limit for the use of certain materials.&lt;SEP&gt;1,000°F is a temperature threshold mentioned in the document for material usage.&lt;SEP&gt;1,000°F is a temperature threshold mentioned in the guidelines for using certain materials.&lt;SEP&gt;1,000°F is a temperature threshold for material usage specifications.&lt;SEP&gt;1,000°F is a temperature value mentioned in the context of ratings for flanges and flanged fittings.</data>
