    <node id="Class 400 Flanges">
      <data key="d0">Class 400 Flanges</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Class 400 Flanges are a standard classification for pipe flanges.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 400 Flanges are used in pipe connections and are described in ASME B16.5-2013 standards.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 400 flanges are a specific class of flanges with certain pressure and temperature ratings.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 400 Flanges are another type of flange used in piping systems, referenced in the context of drilling templates.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 400 Flanges are described in detail in Table II-14 of the ASME B16.5-2013 standard.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 400 Flanges are described in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, detailing their dimensions and specifications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-79c64f1efd29986d7f72185f69bc53da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9041215fae61d5ca6576cebcac22159a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ea1b2e76d1f000d5569b9486b9e5ac4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24c021ba97b00541cab44ee6e76173ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31bc32875a6306edfc4741462637a4e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aa3224b393530e878cd8da41ea17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fddb3381428920d2982f42a7fcc67168</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255073</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Table II-13">
      <data key="d0">Table II-13</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Table II-13 provides stud bolt lengths for flange joints.&lt;SEP&gt;Table II-13 provides templates for drilling Class 400 Flanges, detailing dimensions and specifications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-79c64f1efd29986d7f72185f69bc53da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-163392eb949c4d866fc3a6cbdb8233ab</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255073</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Class 600 Dimensions">
      <data key="d0">Class 600 Dimensions</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Class 600 dimensions are referenced for socket welding flanges in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 600 dimensions are used in specific sizes for flanges, as indicated in the text.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 600 Dimensions are provided in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard for various flange sizes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-79c64f1efd29986d7f72185f69bc53da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ea1b2e76d1f000d5569b9486b9e5ac4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aa3224b393530e878cd8da41ea17</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255073</data>
