    <node id="150">
      <data key="d0">150</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">150 is a temperature value in degrees Celsius, specifically listed in various tables and documents. It is also mentioned as one of the temperature points for working pressure classes and pressure-temperature ratings. The temperature 150°C is associated with different contexts, including being part of a temperature range for working pressure classes and a specific temperature point in the provided data. Additionally, 150 psig is noted as a working pressure class mentioned in the document. While 150 is primarily described as a temperature value in degrees Celsius, it is also referenced as a specific temperature in Fahrenheit and a working pressure class for materials at a particular temperature.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a0109166d44b4066c639726c7a8ccb61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba38e995e9267b01b62ee7faaf352b6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c36c032ac359cde347a031aeec782a7f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9125d75140ea310f02990051dabb25b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-324dc22909af5555deb08d67b96b3e67&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503d8a63fb788455f42315bb7625264d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64169122dd60bf0873c761d69e140ea8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f85b34e2860017c4a2a3af023715b984&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a23bcebd8b470b9a08b539706258ba5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-913ab8bf8d15091a1c354835260c5873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6893a217dc9a544aa14a272dace58707&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c21da8c1a6a154a2c6aadf64e368d44b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7575423eeeae0b9d1868c3a0607f0f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b4364e68825dbe4e5d2b1711332b9ba</data>
