      <data key="d0">800</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">800°C is a temperature point listed in the table.&lt;SEP&gt;800°C is one of the temperature points listed in the table.&lt;SEP&gt;800 is one of the pressure values listed for the 400°F class.&lt;SEP&gt;800 is a pressure temperature rating for a specific material group in ASME B16.5-2013.&lt;SEP&gt;800 is a numerical value.&lt;SEP&gt;800 is a temperature value listed in the table.</data>
