    <node id="400">
      <data key="d0">400</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">400 is a temperature value in degrees Celsius and is listed in various tables and documents. Specifically, 400°C is a temperature point and a temperature range for working pressure classes. It is also one of the temperature points listed for pressure-temperature ratings. Additionally, 400 is a working pressure class, measured in pounds per square inch gauge (psig), applicable to materials at specific temperatures. This working pressure class is mentioned in the document and corresponds to a particular temperature range.</data>
