    <node id="300">
      <data key="d0">300</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">300 is a temperature value listed in various tables and documents, primarily in degrees Celsius (°C). It is also mentioned as a working pressure class in pounds per square inch gauge (psig), specifically 300 psig. This temperature point is part of a range for working pressure classes and is listed alongside other temperature values such as 300°C. Additionally, 300 is noted as a specific temperature in Fahrenheit, though this conversion is not provided here. The temperature 300 is consistently referenced in the context of pressure-temperature ratings and material specifications, indicating its importance in defining operational parameters for certain materials and systems.</data>
