    <node id="600">
      <data key="d0">600</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">600 is a temperature value used in pressure-temperature ratings for materials. Specifically, it is listed as a temperature point in various contexts, including a temperature in degrees Celsius (600°C), a temperature range for working pressure classes, and a temperature point in tables. Additionally, 600 is associated with working pressure classes, such as 600 psig (pounds per square inch gauge), which is mentioned in the document. It is also noted as one of the temperature points listed for the pressure-temperature ratings and the 300°F class. Overall, 600 serves as a critical reference point for determining appropriate working pressure classes for materials under specific temperature conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a0109166d44b4066c639726c7a8ccb61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba38e995e9267b01b62ee7faaf352b6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9125d75140ea310f02990051dabb25b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7074bdf5eed4e53c2fd550a9c7540de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-324dc22909af5555deb08d67b96b3e67&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64169122dd60bf0873c761d69e140ea8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f85b34e2860017c4a2a3af023715b984&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a23bcebd8b470b9a08b539706258ba5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-75a86085ee505a3da722c32886cb08a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-913ab8bf8d15091a1c354835260c5873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6893a217dc9a544aa14a272dace58707&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c21da8c1a6a154a2c6aadf64e368d44b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3418e404eea4379f09843151bbf0eaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7575423eeeae0b9d1868c3a0607f0f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b4364e68825dbe4e5d2b1711332b9ba</data>
