    <node id="Blind Flange">
      <data key="d0">Blind Flange</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">A blind flange is a flat disk used to close off the end of a pipe or vessel.&lt;SEP&gt;Blind Flange is a type of pipe flange used in certain configurations.&lt;SEP&gt;Blind Flange is a flat, disk-shaped fitting used to close off the end of a pipe or vessel.&lt;SEP&gt;Blind flanges may be made with or without hubs at the manufacturer’s option.&lt;SEP&gt;Blind Flange is a type of pipe fitting used in reducing operations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2904771c0741938726758dab221ea2fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c2f5be5ae1269254713641c236d6a28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c860be0c3f5ab97837a33d0776f228db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e063d28a217c52dd27cce9855642fcf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a46bab0c67076b2880139ab335aeabc3</data>
