    <node id="Counterbore">
      <data key="d0">Counterbore</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Counterbore is a recessed area in a flange where a bolt head or nut sits flush with the surface.&lt;SEP&gt;Counterbore measures the depth of the counterbore in the flange.&lt;SEP&gt;Counterbore is a recessed area in a flange designed to accommodate a fastener head.&lt;SEP&gt;Counterbore is a recessed area around a hole, typically to accommodate a flat head screw or bolt.&lt;SEP&gt;Counterbore is the recessed area in the flange for receiving the bolt head.&lt;SEP&gt;Counterbore is a recessed area in a flange where a bolt head sits flush with the surface.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2904771c0741938726758dab221ea2fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31bc32875a6306edfc4741462637a4e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1991062d5c6aa490277d1b30a0762cee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0df2a48018c5815fcbc69ee77e5e9629&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b3b645868407aac7a7956cba998d0e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a46bab0c67076b2880139ab335aeabc3</data>
