    <node id="900">
      <data key="d0">900</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">900 is a temperature value in degrees Celsius and is listed in various tables and documents related to pressure-temperature ratings. Specifically, 900°C is one of the temperature points mentioned in the table, representing a temperature range for working pressure classes. Additionally, 900 is also a working pressure class, expressed in pounds per square inch gauge (psig), applicable for materials at specific temperatures within certain pressure ranges. These pressure classes are crucial for determining the safe operating conditions of materials under high temperatures.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a0109166d44b4066c639726c7a8ccb61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba38e995e9267b01b62ee7faaf352b6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9125d75140ea310f02990051dabb25b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-324dc22909af5555deb08d67b96b3e67&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64169122dd60bf0873c761d69e140ea8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f85b34e2860017c4a2a3af023715b984&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a23bcebd8b470b9a08b539706258ba5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-75a86085ee505a3da722c32886cb08a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6893a217dc9a544aa14a272dace58707&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c21da8c1a6a154a2c6aadf64e368d44b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3418e404eea4379f09843151bbf0eaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7575423eeeae0b9d1868c3a0607f0f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b4364e68825dbe4e5d2b1711332b9ba</data>
