    <node id="538°C">
      <data key="d0">538°C</data>
      <data key="d1">temperature</data>
      <data key="d2">538°C is a significant temperature threshold mentioned across various contexts related to material usage and specifications. Specifically, it is the maximum temperature limit for the use of carbon–molybdenum steel as per ASME International standards. This temperature threshold is also referenced in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, where it is associated with the ratings for flanges and flanged fittings. Additionally, 538°C is noted in the notes for material usage guidelines, particularly in the context of material heat treatment and specific conditions. These references emphasize the importance of adhering to this temperature limit to ensure the safe and effective use of certain materials under high-temperature conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c01da93e68a62ebd162469f786517eea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d852b8bef4bf5e1b06d5eca4665efb0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5768d17437e1d8c24d2ea2f48a09d7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a319dec7b0b61a0bc319c91c99c9a587&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0da4a394d3be37c8a59a24dd838d13b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d2c522c8854e3aa2e96dab1c0fb5599&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf336e9994ced99fe215bd678411af07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc7860e55d358ba95ec0400c2fc4014e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8689b4c902ee495b0f8e912c7a0a9582&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a23bcebd8b470b9a08b539706258ba5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-913ab8bf8d15091a1c354835260c5873</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255078</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
