    <node id="2500">
      <data key="d0">2500</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">2500 is a temperature in degrees Celsius and also a working pressure class in pounds per square inch (psi). It appears as a temperature point and a working pressure class in various contexts, including pressure-temperature ratings and material specifications. Specifically, 2500°C is part of a temperature range for working pressure classes, while 2500 psig is a working pressure class mentioned in the document. Additionally, 2500 is listed as a temperature point and a working pressure class in tables and for specific materials at particular temperatures.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ba38e995e9267b01b62ee7faaf352b6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9125d75140ea310f02990051dabb25b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-324dc22909af5555deb08d67b96b3e67&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64169122dd60bf0873c761d69e140ea8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f85b34e2860017c4a2a3af023715b984&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a23bcebd8b470b9a08b539706258ba5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6893a217dc9a544aa14a272dace58707&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7575423eeeae0b9d1868c3a0607f0f9</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
