    <node id="Taper">
      <data key="d0">Taper</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Taper is a term used to describe the angle of the hub, with a maximum of 7 degrees for certain types of flanges.&lt;SEP&gt;Taper refers to the taper angle of flanges, with a maximum of 7 degrees for certain types.&lt;SEP&gt;Taper refers to the gradual reduction in diameter along the length of a hub, not exceeding 7 degrees for certain types of flanges.&lt;SEP&gt;Taper refers to the gradual reduction in diameter along the length of a threaded or lapped flange.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-dd9487a2f3662945039d8bc799ee92b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d8ab581faa40c9c1eb52a6a9307019c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32c51ff12b3c72377950aac97432147f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aa3224b393530e878cd8da41ea17</data>
