    <node id="1500">
      <data key="d0">1500</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">1500 is a temperature point in degrees Celsius and is also used as a working pressure class in various contexts. Specifically, 1500°C is part of a temperature range for working pressure classes, and 1500 is one of the temperature points listed for pressure-temperature ratings. Additionally, 1500 psig (pounds per square inch gauge) is a working pressure class mentioned in the document, and 1500 °F (degrees Fahrenheit) is another temperature point referenced. The term 1500 is also used as a working pressure class in psi (pounds per square inch) for a specific temperature range and for the material at a particular temperature. Furthermore, 1500 is listed as a pressure class in the table provided.</data>
