    <node id="1996 Edition">
      <data key="d0">1996 Edition</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The 1996 Edition of ASME B16.5 allowed flanges marked with multiple material grades, revised flange facing finish requirements, and updated pressure-temperature ratings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-545818ef44ac301232f6e8003ced593b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255080</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="2003 Edition">
      <data key="d0">2003 Edition</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The 2003 Edition of ASME B16.5 included metric units as primary reference units, maintained U.S. Customary units, and revised flange thickness designations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-545818ef44ac301232f6e8003ced593b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255080</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="2009 Edition">
      <data key="d0">2009 Edition</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The 2009 Edition of ASME B16.5 added new materials, updated pressure-temperature ratings, and designated annexes as mandatory and nonmandatory appendices.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-545818ef44ac301232f6e8003ced593b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255080</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="2013 Edition">
      <data key="d0">2013 Edition</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The 2013 Edition of ASME B16.5 revised the Materials paragraph and included perpendicularity tolerances.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-545818ef44ac301232f6e8003ced593b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776255080</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="B16 Standards Committee">
      <data key="d0">B16 Standards Committee</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The B16 Standards Committee is responsible for developing and maintaining standards related to valves, flanges, fittings, and gaskets.&lt;SEP&gt;B16 Standards Committee is a committee that holds regular meetings and is governed by ASME procedures.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-545818ef44ac301232f6e8003ced593b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da0eb2037f412344871720430fa6cf02</data>
