    <node id="Lateral">
      <data key="d0">Lateral</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Lateral is a measurement concept used in flanged fittings dimensions.&lt;SEP&gt;Lateral refers to a measurement or dimension in the context of flanged fittings.&lt;SEP&gt;Lateral is a term used in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard to describe certain fitting configurations.&lt;SEP&gt;Lateral refers to a direction perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of a pipe.&lt;SEP&gt;Lateral is a type of fitting mentioned in the standard document.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-76864809d8f49cc522affb8d29d2289a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b198cbe23ec845253cfd2861d7fc5756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38e654cf4e95cce3ba3e7cced9c476f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7d66f91fd341a23e68eadbefdb9b7ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b2ad87c358f78ef6fe44833b9f86e79</data>
