    <node id="Welding Neck Flanges">
      <data key="d0">Welding Neck Flanges</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Welding neck flanges are designed to have a hub thickness at least equal to that calculated for pipe having 276 MPa (40,000 psi) specified minimum yield strength.&lt;SEP&gt;Welding neck flanges are referenced in the standard, with specific sections dedicated to their details.&lt;SEP&gt;Welding Neck Flanges are pipe flanges with a short neck that allows for welding to the pipe.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f28c7d4bdd4e434720bb2e0817acb7da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15d13d8a9cf127681d0ef72c7289a815&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aa3224b393530e878cd8da41ea17</data>
