      <data key="d0">Chamfer</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Chamfer is a beveled edge or corner on a part, often used to reduce stress concentrations.&lt;SEP&gt;Chamfer is a beveled edge or corner, often found at the beginning of a hub or neck in flanges.&lt;SEP&gt;Chamfer is a measurement related to the angle cut to reduce stress concentration.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-edfa2a8d33668f4d57dbfceea1fab17e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0df2a48018c5815fcbc69ee77e5e9629&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ee06a2df0130f4a0dc8ec87fdc1d0c4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6962408b774fe5ab78bfedcf807dfe29</data>
