    <node id="Reducing Threaded and Slip-On Flanges">
      <data key="d0">Reducing Threaded and Slip-On Flanges</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Reducing Threaded and Slip-On Flanges are specialized pipe fittings designed to reduce the size of a pipe while maintaining either a threaded or slip-on connection. These flanges are detailed in Table 6 and covered in Table II-6 of the ASME B16.5-2013 standard. They are characterized by specific dimensions and are described in various documents. Reducing Threaded and Slip-On Flanges are essentially flanges with reduced dimensions, used to achieve a smaller pipe size while ensuring compatibility with threading or slip-on connections.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7ea1b2e76d1f000d5569b9486b9e5ac4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd9487a2f3662945039d8bc799ee92b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edfa2a8d33668f4d57dbfceea1fab17e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65bb92edfd06205fa901097f136f3ce0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1991062d5c6aa490277d1b30a0762cee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c860be0c3f5ab97837a33d0776f228db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45ef876ea0243f68770603a1cadf892b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e063d28a217c52dd27cce9855642fcf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a46bab0c67076b2880139ab335aeabc3</data>
