    <node id="Lapped">
      <data key="d0">Lapped</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Lapped is a term used in the context of flange joints.&lt;SEP&gt;Lapped refers to a method of joining pipes where the edges of the pipe and fitting are overlapped and then welded.&lt;SEP&gt;Lapped indicates the lapped joint configuration of the flange.&lt;SEP&gt;Lapped refers to a specific method of flange welding where the edges are overlapped.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-99a1e3e75d92d69d9c4e1104e9aee33d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45ef876ea0243f68770603a1cadf892b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b3b645868407aac7a7956cba998d0e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6962408b774fe5ab78bfedcf807dfe29</data>
