    <node id="Outside Diameter">
      <data key="d0">Outside Diameter</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Outside Diameter is the external measurement of a pipe or component, which is a crucial dimension used in various applications such as flanges and fittings. This measurement specifically refers to the external circumference of a pipe or joint, and it is also a key dimension for flange ends and hubs. Outside Diameter is typically measured around the outer edge of the flange, providing a precise external circumference that is essential for ensuring proper fit and functionality in piping systems. This concept is fundamental in defining the size and specifications of pipes and components used in plumbing, mechanical engineering, and other industries where precise measurements are critical.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-98e6bd64e65f31d06ced3b3e90f47312&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b5b0e2acae20a65c1c3b15054804a3f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edfa2a8d33668f4d57dbfceea1fab17e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10054c6a90c7e34cf9ec3260463671fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1991062d5c6aa490277d1b30a0762cee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0df2a48018c5815fcbc69ee77e5e9629&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b3d3983136bf26d485546eb760e1ee8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea77e5de59087d497604a8e25484020&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3abc323d58495b8071ec97d17500fa8</data>
